  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2021-03-18",
    "date": "2022-02-08T23:30:42Z",
    "text": "Stop Shielding Culpable Platforms Act\n\n This bill modifies provisions relating to the liability of a provider or user of an interactive computer service (e.g., a social media company) for material placed on its platform by another information content provider.\n\nUnder current law, a provider or user of an interactive computer service is not considered the publisher or speaker of any information provided by another information content provider. The bill specifies that a provider or user of an interactive computer service may still be treated as a distributor of such information."
  },
